A fisherman was attacked and killed by a hippo in Lake Naivasha as cases of human-wildlife conflict rise. The man succumbed to injuries at the Naivasha Sub-county Hospital. His colleague escaped narrowly after the lone animal also attacked him during a fishing expedition along South Lake. The two were setting up their nets along the shores of the lake when the animal moved in, crushing the fisherman&rsquo;s leg before going for his colleague. &nbsp;A witness, Peter Kamau, said the second man escaped with minor injuries to his hands and sought help from other fishermen. &nbsp; &nbsp; READ MORE Boy dies in Naivasha excursion after KCPE exams